title: AttributeError: module 'tensorflow.python.training.checkpointable' has no attribute 'CheckpointableBase'
body_html:
This problem has been posted before but the response does not help - there is no tf.nightly in my environment.

This same code worked before.

In the base Anaconda environment it said that tf did not have the following attributes: keras and version.

I created a new environment (COS801) in Anaconda.

This is the code:

import tensorflow as tf
